{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: PR-change discovery -> file selection -> analyzer input. A unit test of only a filter function can miss wiring bugs (e.g., wrong path normalization between modules). Higher levels were considered and rejected: behavior text focuses on \"files changed in the pull request\" selection logic, not real network/OS timing/subprocess behavior, and has no AI dependency.","test_description":"Wire changed-file provider, selection pipeline, and analyzer input collector in-process; feed a mixed repo fixture (changed + unchanged) and assert analyzer receives only changed paths.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real risk is across modules: linter findings -> severity bucketer -> comment renderer/post payload. Unit-testing only grouping logic can miss serialization/template mismatches. Higher levels rejected: behavior text is about grouping/content structure, not real GitHub API transport semantics, and no model output is involved.","test_description":"Run findings through aggregator + comment-builder + PR-comment client adapter with a fake client, then assert posted payload contains correct severity sections and finding placement.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is explicitly an environment/time-budget guarantee tied to GitHub Actions runtime. Mocked linter/runtime would hide real I/O, process startup, and runner performance effects. Rejection of lower levels is disqualified by behavior text: \"completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.\"","test_description":"Execute the lint step end-to-end on a 200-file fixture using the real action entrypoint and real linter invocation in CI-like runtime; assert total wall-clock stays below 10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.95,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on real subprocess failure semantics (\"linter process crashes\"). In-process mocks can miss crash mode details (exit signal/code, partial output handling, process isolation) that affect continuation logic. No AI dependency; single pipeline step, so not Workflow.","test_description":"Run real lint orchestrator against a batch containing one crash-inducing malformed file and multiple valid files; verify crash is isolated, remaining files are analyzed, and final PR results payload is still produced.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Core failure is deterministic dedup key logic (rule overlap, same file/line) and can be caught at a single-function/object boundary without I/O. Higher levels rejected by behavior text: it specifies dedup semantics in output, not external infra or model judgment.","test_description":"Test dedup function/object with synthetic findings containing same file+line+message from overlappin